Request Assessment:
- Identify what data needs to be recovered
- Determine data location (local drive, network share, cloud storage, email)
- Establish when the data was lost or deleted
- Assess urgency and business impact

Data Recovery Eligibility:
- Check backup retention policy periods
- Verify if data falls within recovery window
- Identify appropriate backup source
- Confirm user authorization for recovery

{% if source == 'local_drive' %}
Local Drive Recovery:
- Check Windows Recycle Bin first
- Look for File History/Previous Versions
- Access backup software agent on device
- Request restore from latest available backup
- Consider data recovery tools if not in backup
{% endif %}

{% if source == 'network_share' %}
Network Share Recovery:
- Check for Volume Shadow Copy availability
- Access Previous Versions on the share
- Submit restore request to backup team
- Specify exact path, filename, and date needed
- Verify permissions to restore location
{% endif %}

{% if source == 'onedrive_sharepoint' %}
OneDrive/SharePoint Recovery:
- Check OneDrive/SharePoint Recycle Bin
- Check Site Collection Recycle Bin (second-stage)
- Review Version History for the file
- Restore previous version if available
- Use OneDrive/SharePoint admin restore if needed
{% endif %}

{% if source == 'email' %}
Email Recovery:
- Check Deleted Items folder
- Check Recoverable Items folder (Outlook)
- Request mailbox restore from backup
- Specify date range and folders needed
- Consider eDiscovery search if specific emails needed
{% endif %}

{% if source == 'database' %}
Database Recovery:
- Identify database and table affected
- Determine point-in-time for recovery
- Coordinate with DBA team
- Request restore to non-production environment first
- Verify data integrity before production restore
{% endif %}

Recovery Execution:
- Initiate restore to alternate location (not overwrite)
- Monitor restore job progress
- Verify recovered data integrity
- Confirm correct version/date was restored

Data Delivery:
- Move recovered data to user's accessible location
- Verify user can access recovered files
- Confirm data matches user's requirements
- Clean up temporary restore location

Documentation:
- Document what was recovered and from when
- Note any data that could not be recovered
- Record time taken for recovery
- Update user on backup protection going forward
